{
  "texts": [
    "It is specifically designed for tasks that require the output to be a distinct or classified value, such as binary classification [17].",
    "Gaussian Naive Bayes (GNB) is a Gaussian distribution-based statistical categorization method.",
    "It operates under the assumption that each factor influences the possibility of the result separately, summing the likelihoods to determine the most likely category [18].",
    "Additionally, Support Vector Machine (SVM) is a technique that operates by identifying a separating hyperplane between various classes by converting the data into a higher-dimensional space.",
    "Even in cases when the data are not linearly separable in the original space, this technique works well [19]."
  ]
}